text.__SUMMARY__: Odostomia tasmanica, common name the Tasmania pyramid-shell,  is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyramidellidae, the pyrams and their allies.
text.Description: The length of the shell measures 2 mm.
text.Distribution: This endemic species occurs in the littoral zone and offshore  off Tasmania, the Bass Strait, New South Wales and Victoria.
text.References:
OBIS : Odostomia tasmanica
CF Laseron, The Family Pyramidellidae (Mollusca) from Northern Australia, Australian Journal of Marine and Freshwater Research 10(2) 177 - 268
